VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stuff that we did for characters, except this time for world building. So, we just copy in the prompt here and then let it go. All right, so it is finished doing our world building, so I can go ahead and copy that and once again,'

[12:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'place it into our document here, world building sheet. This next step is going to involve a few more steps before we finish out step two of developing the story bible. And that is the novel'

[13:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'outliner. So, the prompt goes something like this. It\'s actually shorter, but it says, "Using the story dossier, character sheet, world building sheet, and plot template, generate a fully fleshed-out outline for this short story. Make sure to use the outline'

[13:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'template to inform you on the kind of things that should happen in the chapters you are outlining. The summary for each chapter should have specific details rather than vague allusions to what should happen. Make it as though you were going to hand it off to a ghostwriter to write the first draft.'

[13:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Make sure you follow the template extremely carefully. Only include the asked for details or outline details. Do not add any preamble commentary or anything other than what I\'ve asked for above. So we\'ll go ahead and save that. So you noticed at the top it said using the story dossier, the character sheet,'

[13:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the world-building sheet, and the plot template. So we want to make sure we got all of those things first. Now in the project\'s settings you can add files here. And this is where we\'re going to'

