[25:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'smelled worse and Fern Hollow smelled like neither of these. First of all, this feels a bit of a run-on sentence to me. I don\'t necessarily like having this kind of AI likes to start with these sort of sensory details first, kind of'

[25:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'setting the scene, but it\'s often unnecessary. And if I look at the next step, Elara stopped in the inn\'s front step and breathed in rain-damp cobblestone, something green underneath it, not a smell she had a name for, more of a quality, the the way air changes'

[25:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'near the forest. We\'re talking about smell again here, so I actually really don\'t think this is necessary. I would probably add breathe in the smell. And then I would just take this first'

[26:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sentence and remove it entirely. Elara stopped on the inn\'s front steps and breathed in the smell. That sentence is fine now. Rain-damp cobblestone, AI, especially more recent AI models, like to have these like short punctuated'

[26:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sentences, which is sometimes good, it kind of breaks things up, but I don\'t think we need that, so we could just say rain-damp cobblestone and something under green underneath it. And then I\'ll put a period there. And'

[26:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually, this should probably be one sentence. So, I\'d put a colon and then rain-damp cobblestone because otherwise that would have been an incomplete sentence, which isn\'t necessarily a bad thing all the time, but there you have it. And so now we have our first'

[26:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sentence, Elara stopped on the inn\'s front step and breathed in the smell. Rain-damp cobblestone and something green underneath it. Now, this doesn\'t feel like the most exciting sentence. I might consider changing it, but seeing as this is a cozy fantasy, we want to get across that it\'s a cozy fantasy'

[26:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'immediately as as soon as possible. And I think this sentence does that because we have like rain-damp cobblestone, we have the inn, and something green underneath it, right? Now, this next sentence, "Not a smell she had a name for, more a quality the way air changed'

[27:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'near a forest." This is an AI-ism right here where it says, "Not this, but this." Not a smell she had a name for, but more a quality. I usually like to change these if I can. So, I\'d say I\'d probably just rewrite this entire'

[27:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sentence to something like, "She loved the way the air changed near a forest." So, we\'ve got that changes near a forest element, but, you know, that\'s all we need. Then I\'d probably start a new'

[27:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'paragraph because, why not? "The Sylvan Woods began somewhere past the town\'s eastern edge. Whatever slow magic accumulated in the old-growth trees, it reached this far." "She filed this away without deciding what to do with it."'

[27:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The first sentence is good, I think. But, the "She filed this away without deciding what to do with it." I feel like the second half of that sentence is unnecessary. So, I\'ll just delete that. She just filed this away. We don\'t need to say that she didn\'t know what to do'

[27:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with it. She had one bag, she had the solicitor\'s letter. It\'s creases worn to the softness of old cloth from a month of handling. So, there\'s repetitiveness here. She had one bag, she had the solicitor\'s letter. So, I would say she had one bag, colon, the solicitor\'s'

[28:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'letter. "It\'s creases worn to softness of old cloth from a month of handling." Yeah, that\'s fine. It\'s a little wordy, but I think I would leave that. Also, you don\'t have to do a colon here. Colons can sometimes, I don\'t know, uh be a little jarring, particularly in'

[28:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'certain genres. Uh so, you could just use a comma there if you wanted to. She had one bag, the solicitor\'s letter. In fact, I think that\'s actually better myself, so I\'m going to leave it that way. You see what I\'m doing here? Like, I\'m clearly making it my own. Now, this'

[28:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is still a lot of work. I would have gone through this a lot faster if I weren\'t explaining it out loud like I am. Uh over time, you will get better at this process. But, I do strongly recommend you go through it because you'

[28:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can significantly improve the quality of the AI output by doing this and make it a lot more your own. It\'ll also help with AI detection, which is not really an issue, but some people are concerned about it, as well as your right to'

